nodes.documentation:
@title Circular buffer for `uint`s.
 * @notice This contract represents a circular buffer that stores `uint`s. When
        a set number of `uint`s have been stored, the storage starts
        overwriting older entries. It overwrites always the oldest entry in
        the buffer.
nodes.name: CircularBufferUint

typeDescriptions.typeString: literal_string "The max number of items to store in a circular buffer must be greater than 0."

arguments.value: The max number of items to store in a circular buffer must be greater than 0.

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "The max number of items to store in a circular buffer must be greater than 0."

typeDescriptions.typeString: literal_string "Circular buffer size can be setup once."

arguments.value: Circular buffer size can be setup once.

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "Circular buffer size can be setup once."

nodes.documentation:
@notice Setup buffer with the size `_maxItems`.
     * @param _maxItems Defines how many items this buffer stores before
                 overwriting older items.
     * \pre The function can be called only once.
\pre `_maxItems` must be greater than 0.
     * \post Sets up max number of items to be maintained by this buffer.
nodes.name: setupCircularBuffer

nodes.documentation:
@notice Store a new item in the circular buffer.
     * @param _item The item to store in the circular buffer.
     * @return overwrittenItem_ The item that was in the circular buffer's
                         position where the new item is now stored. The
                         overwritten item is no longer available in the
                         circular buffer.
nodes.name: store

nodes.documentation:
@notice Get the most recent item that was stored in the circular buffer.
     * @return head_ The most recently stored item.
nodes.name: head
nextIndex
